fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.store.adapter

Class TransientStoreAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.store.adapter.AbstractStoreAdapter
      • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.store.adapter.TransientStoreAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Saveable, StoreAdapter, Closeable, AutoCloseable, Copiable<StoreAdapter>, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.InternalEObject.EStore

    @Immutable
 @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class TransientStoreAdapter
extends AbstractStoreAdapter
    A StoreAdapter, bound to a Resource.Internal, that caches the rebuilt PersistentEObjects. Its content is shared among all the dependencies that use it, i.e. each Resource.Internal has its own cache.

    This adapter is used in a transient context, when PersistentEObjects are not attached to a PersistentResource.

    See Also:
    PersistentEObject
